dc:title: Taken from the hill up back of the hotel whgere we stayed--two-story building in center foreground. Toward the right. the ruins of Baalbek/ Temple of the Sun and Temple of Bacchus easily identified. Modern village off to the right. In the distance, especially to the left, the plain nearly covered with fruit trees. In the further distance, the snow-capped Lebanons, but unfortunately mostly masked by rising fog. Old cypress tree at the right. Size, 91/2 x 25 1/2 in.
Paper
dc:creator: Swain, George R
